result.execSummary:
The defendant Courtney Ann Lundquist was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:28 AM Prosecuting attorney Brenda L. Yaskal in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Courtney A Lundquist not in court.  Attorney Gibson D Hatch in court for Courtney A Lundquist. Cases called: 20 CM 518 and 22 CM 29, State requesting warrant, Court authorizes warrant.  11:13 am.  Court recalled 20CM518 and 22CM29. Appearances the same with the addition of defendant present.  DA Yaskal recited agreement.  Defendant plead no contest to count 1 in 20CM518 and to count 1 in 22CM29.  Rights and elements.  Court accepted the pleas and found defendant guilty of count 1 in 20CM518 and count 1 in 22CM29; judgments to be entered.  Counts 2 and 3 in 22CM29 dismissed but read in.  Sentencing statements. For count 1 in 20CM518 and Count 1 in 22CM29, Court withheld sentence and placed defendant on probation for 24 months for each count; conditions of probation to include pay costs of $443 for each count, Complete an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommendations; complete any counseling recommended by probation agent; complete DNA sample.  20CM518, 2 days sentence credit and for 22CM29, 12 days sentence credit.  Warrants cancelled in both cases.  Adjourned at 11:29 AM.
